Django: Basic → Advanced (Placement & Industry Level Guide)

Django is a high-level web framework for Python used to build secure and scalable web applications quickly. It follows the MTV architecture (Model–Template–View) which is a variation of MVC.

Many large companies use Django because it provides:

Fast development

Built-in security

Clean architecture

Powerful admin panel

Companies using Django include Instagram, Pinterest, Mozilla, and Spotify.

1️⃣ Django Fundamentals (Beginner Level)

What is Django?

Django is an open-source Python web framework used for backend development. It helps developers build web applications faster with less code.

Key features:

Built-in admin panel

ORM for database interaction

Authentication system

URL routing

Security features

2️⃣ Django Architecture (MTV Pattern)

Django uses the MTV architecture.

Component	Meaning	Purpose
Model	Database structure	Manages data
Template	HTML UI	Displays data
View	Business logic	Processes requests

Flow of a Django request:

User Request
     ↓
URL
     ↓
View
     ↓
Model
     ↓
Template
     ↓
Response

3️⃣ Django Installation

Install Django using pip:

pip install django

Create a new project:

django-admin startproject myproject

Run the server:

python manage.py runserver

Open browser:

http://127.0.0.1:8000

