6️⃣ Models (Database)

Models define database structure.

Example:

from django.db import models

class Post(models.Model):

    title = models.CharField(max_length=100)

    content = models.TextField()

    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)

Run migrations:

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

7️⃣ Django ORM (Database Queries)

Django ORM allows you to interact with the database without writing SQL.

Examples:

Post.objects.all()

Post.objects.filter(title="Django")

Post.objects.get(id=1)

Create object:

Post.objects.create(title="Hello", content="Django tutorial")

8️⃣ Views (Application Logic)

Function-based view example:

from django.http import HttpResponse

def home(request):

    return HttpResponse("Hello Django")

9️⃣ URL Routing

Example:

from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [

    path('', views.home)

]

🔟 Templates (Frontend)

Templates are HTML files used to display data.

Example template:

<h1>{{ title }}</h1>

Example view:

from django.shortcuts import render

def home(request):

    return render(request, "home.html", {"title": "Welcome"})

1️⃣1️⃣ Django Admin Panel

Create admin user:

python manage.py createsuperuser

Register model:

from django.contrib import admin
from .models import Post

admin.site.register(Post)

Admin panel:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin

1️⃣2️⃣ Advanced Django Concepts
Class-Based Views
from django.views import View
from django.http import HttpResponse

class HomeView(View):

    def get(self, request):

        return HttpResponse("Hello Django")
Authentication System

Django provides built-in authentication.

Example:

from django.contrib.auth import authenticate, login

user = authenticate(username=username, password=password)

login(request, user)

Features:

Login

Logout

Signup

Permissions

REST API Development

For APIs Django commonly uses Django REST Framework.

Install:

pip install djangorestframework

Example API:

from rest_framework.decorators import api_view
from rest_framework.response import Response

@api_view(['GET'])

def api(request):

    return Response({"message":"Hello API"})

